{"article_id":"vZix3nLiFroDwIri","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Israel 's Election :","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"Exit Polls Show","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"Netanyahu 's Likud , Opposition In Tight Race","depth":4},{"id":3,"text":"Exit polls","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"released after the close of voting in Israel 's national election","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"show","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"that the race is too close to call .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"Israel 's Channel 1 and Channel 10 both said","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu 's Likud party and Isaac Herzog 's Zionist Union secured 27 seats each in the 120-seat Knesset .","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"Channel 2 , meanwhile , have Likud 28 seats","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"and the Zionist Union 27 .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"The numbers were published by Haaretz .","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"What that is likely to mean is ,","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"as NPR 's Emily Harris tells our Newscast unit ,","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"Israel 's new government wo n't be immediately known .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"`` The new government will need approval from a majority of the newly elected parliament .","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"No party has ever won a straight majority in Israel ,","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"so the leader of the party with the most votes gets several weeks to try to negotiate a coalition among parties with sometimes very different agendas .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"For a while during this tight race , there was talk","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"that the center-left Zionist Union party","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"led by Yitzak Herzog","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"and the center-right Likud party","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"led by Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"could potentially join the same government .","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"Netanyahu ruled that out in the last days of campaigning . ''","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"And , the Israeli prime minister , in a Facebook post , claimed","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"a `` great victory against all odds . ''","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"Herzog , meanwhile , told his supporters :","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"`` These results will bring Labor back into power . ''","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"He called the results a `` big victory for the Labor Party ,","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"which has n't done this well","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"since Yitzhak Rabin won in 1992 . ''","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"The comments were reported by Haaretz .","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"He added","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"that a negotiating team has been formed in an effort","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"to form a government .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and his Likud party face challenges from the left and right in today 's Israeli elections","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"-","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"in which approaches to a potential Palestinian state and the economy have emerged as top issues .","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"`` Netanyahu trailed in the final opinion polls [ behind ] the center-left Zionist Union ticket ,","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"which says","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"it will focus on economic issues and trying to restart peace negotiations with the Palestinians , ''","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"NPR 's Emily Harris reports from Jerusalem .","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"`` Hours before voting started ,","depth":8},{"id":44,"text":"Netanyahu came out against a Palestinian state at this time","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"- a position","depth":8},{"id":46,"text":"long held by his main rival on the right . ''","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"The voting began this morning","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"and will continue until 10 p.m. local time ;","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"that 's when the first exit poll results should come out","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"- around 4 p.m . ET .","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"Israel 's Election :","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"Exit Polls Show","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"Netanyahu 's Likud , Opposition In Tight Race","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"Listen · 2:40","depth":5},{"id":55,"text":"2:40","depth":5},{"id":56,"text":"Israeli newspaper Haaretz is live-blogging today 's vote ;","depth":4},{"id":57,"text":"it reports","depth":6},{"id":58,"text":"that in the first three hours","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"of polls","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"being open ,","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"nearly 14 percent of eligible voters had cast their ballots .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"It adds","depth":6},{"id":63,"text":"that the rate is `` 20 percent higher '' than the previous two elections .","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"Netanyahu has been the focus of controversy over his recent speech to a joint meeting of the U.S. Congress , a trip","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"that deepened tensions with the White House .","depth":6},{"id":66,"text":"The prime minister 's opponents seized on the opportunity","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"to say","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"they would work to strengthen ties with America 's leaders","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"to ensure their country 's security .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"Emily tells Morning Edition","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"that","depth":7},{"id":72,"text":"if his party does n't win outright ,","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"Netanyahu could still remain in power .","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"`` Even if his Likud party does n't emerge with the most votes , ''","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"she says ,","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"`` he could be the one","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"who could negotiate successfully among the 11 or 12 parties","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"that are supposed to get in parliament ,","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"and build a coalition government out of that , with him at the helm . ''","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"Because election day is a holiday in Israel ,","depth":4},{"id":81,"text":"many people are expected to get outdoors","depth":5},{"id":82,"text":"to take advantage of what the Haaretz newspaper says","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"will be nice weather .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":167,"left":134,"right":166,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":134,"left":86,"right":133,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":86,"left":0,"right":85,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":85,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":133,"left":118,"right":132,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":94,"right":117,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":89,"right":93,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":89,"left":88,"right":6,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":88,"left":87,"right":5,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":87,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":93,"left":92,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":92,"left":90,"right":91,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":90,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":91,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":117,"left":99,"right":116,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":96,"right":98,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":12,"right":95,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":95,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":98,"left":15,"right":97,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":116,"left":107,"right":115,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":107,"left":105,"right":106,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":104,"right":24,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":104,"left":18,"righ